Subject: Narrative Subject File Index

Description: Contract for mapping narrative-layer subject matters to files of interest for re-entry, search, and deeper inquiry.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\attention_layers\NarrativeDigestion.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\attention_layers\SubjectInquiry.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\attention_layers\LayeredActivationInspection.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SurfacePeripheryInquiryIndex.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SemanticHashIndex.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_narrative_subject_file_index\Dictated_Narrative_Subject_File_Index_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric.sop

& [NarrativeSubjectFileIndex] is the narrative-subject-to-file-interest contract
  + [narrated_subject] is a subject matter named or implied by narrative, reflection, operating-loop tick, periphery realization, or source-preserved user direction
  + [narrative_subject_key] is the stable normalized key for a narrated subject
  + [file_of_interest] is a local SOP file worth opening when re-entering or deepening that narrated subject
  + [file_interest_relation] is why the file matters to the narrated subject
  + [primary_file_interest_set] is directly cited, governing, source-bearing, or canonical files to open first
  + [secondary_file_interest_set] is adjacent, supporting, analogous, or weakly associated files to keep available as internal periphery
  + [file_association_strength] is primary, secondary, weak_nearby, unresolved, or outside
  + [subject_file_table] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\indexes\NarrativeSubjectFileTable.sop
  + [subject_file_entry] is one subject key with file pointers, relation reasons, search phrases, depth hints, and outside limits
  + [framework_periphery_set] is the named larger framework context visible around the subject
  + [depth_hint] is surface, hair, skin, pressure, impact, or deep_probe
  + [coverage_status] is seed, partial, reviewed, stale, unresolved, or outside
  + [reentry_use] is search guidance for Codex, local workers, narrative digestion, and trailing checksum review
  + [residual_outside] is unindexed narrative subjects, stale paths, unsupported authority, and exhaustive coverage claims

  = must: map narrated subjects to files of interest without absorbing those files into the narrative layer
  = must: preserve relation_reason so later attention knows why the file is relevant
  = must: preserve depth_hint so focus can decide whether to skim, inspect, or deep-probe
  = must: keep files_of_interest as search and re-entry guidance, not proof of semantic identity
  = must: distinguish directly cited files from inferred support files
  = must: distinguish primary_file_interest_set from secondary_file_interest_set when the entry feeds internal periphery
  = must: keep file_association_strength as guidance, not proof
  = must: preserve framework_periphery_set as named context for deeper activation inspection
  = must: preserve unindexed, stale, or weakly supported subjects as outside
  = should: prefer local C:\Project\Pinky\.sop paths over historical F:\.sop paths
  = should: update the table when a narrative record, tick, or periphery realization becomes a surface for future work
  - never: claim complete project coverage from a seed table
  - never: let narrative subject lookup override source authority, evidence gates, or runtime validator boundaries

& [NarrativeSubjectFileEntryShape] is one table entry shape
  + [subject_key] is the normalized narrative subject
  + [narrative_surface] is the narrative record, tick, source, or state file where the subject is active
  + [file_interest_set] is the files to open first for that subject
  + [primary_file_interest_set] is the strongest file-interest pointers for first inspection
  + [secondary_file_interest_set] is weaker nearby pointers for later or wider inspection
  + [relation_reason_set] is why each file belongs to the subject
  + [search_phrase_set] is local phrases to search in those files
  + [framework_periphery_set] is the named larger framework context that may be admitted through LayeredActivationInspection
  + [depth_hint] is the attention depth to spend on re-entry
  + [coverage_status] is how trustworthy or complete the entry is
  + [outside] is what the entry does not prove

  = must: keep the subject key compact and stable
  = must: include at least one narrative_surface or evidence path
  = must: separate file_interest_set from authority claims
  = must: preserve primary and secondary file interest when a subject becomes internal periphery
  = must: keep framework_periphery_set as periphery until LayeredActivationInspection admits a bounded declaration window
  = should: include a later_review_trigger when the subject is hot but under-indexed

& [NarrativeSubjectIndexProcedure] is the operating pass for using the index
  + [input] is narrative_subject, active_focal_point, narrative_surface, depth_need, and periphery_draw
  + [output] is selected_file_interest_set, relation_reason_set, unresolved_subjects, and residual_outside

  = step_1: identify narrated subject matters in the active narrative, tick, realization, or user direction
  = step_2: normalize each narrated subject into a narrative_subject_key
  = step_3: collect directly cited files and inferred support files
  = step_4: classify each file_interest_relation as source, contract, state, event, index, runtime, evidence, blocker, support, analogy, or outside
  = step_4b: classify each file_of_interest as primary, secondary, weak_nearby, unresolved, or outside for SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric
  = step_5: select depth_hint from the attention weight scale and current faculty depth
  = step_6: hand selected file_interest_set to SubjectInquiryLayer for inspection queue formation
  = step_7: query NarrativeSubjectFileTable before broad repository search
  = step_8: route selected files through SurfacePeripheryInquiryIndex and SemanticHashIndex when deeper term lookup is needed
  = step_9: preserve missing targets, stale paths, and speculative relations as outside

& [NarrativeSubjectFileMarkerShape] is the compact marker a narrative surface may expose
  + [narrative_surface_key] is the file-local handle for the narrative surface
  + [narrative_surface_file] is the SOP file containing the narrative surface
  + [subject_key_set] is narrated subjects exposed for lookup
  + [subject_file_table] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\indexes\NarrativeSubjectFileTable.sop
  + [lookup_ready_subject_set] is subjects with table entries
  + [unresolved_subject_set] is subjects with insufficient file-interest mapping
  + [promotion_rule] is query the table only when focus, periphery draw, checksum review, or runtime registry re-entry asks for that subject

  = must: keep narrative surface markers compact
  = must: avoid turning every mentioned word into a subject
  = must: prefer subjects that shape purpose, evidence, boundary, or next action

(narrative_subject_file_index) :narrated_subject: /file_interest_boundary/ |unindexed_subject|
  + [narrated_subject] is the subject matter named by narrative or reflection
  + [file_interest_boundary] is direct citation, support relation, source lineage, table entry, relation reason, depth hint, and local authority path
  + [unindexed_subject] is a narrated subject without reliable file pointers or with stale, speculative, or overbroad mapping
  = inside: subject key, narrative surface, file interest set, relation reason, search phrase, depth hint, and coverage status
  = boundary: local Pinky .sop authority, source preservation, evidence paths, surface lookup, semantic hash lookup, and outside preservation
  |outside| proof of meaning, exhaustive coverage, hidden cognition, remote authority, stale path certainty, and automatic action
